        "text": "Julia Roberts is opening up about her family life.\n\nOn the Today show Monday, the star of the new film Leave the World Behind called husband Danny Moder “our anchor” when asked about life as a parent.\n\n“It all starts with Danny Moder,” Roberts, 56, told Hoda Kotb. The father of twins Hazel Patricia and Phinnaeus Walter, 19, and Henry Daniel, 16, is “our person and in the most beautiful way, the captain of our ship,” said the actress.\n\n“For me, understanding how deeply felt life could be,” she added, “really started with him.”\n\nThe Erin Brockovich Oscar winner and Moder have been married since 2002, after meeting and working together on the set of The Mexican. Their two older children are away at college, Roberts told Kotb when she and her Leave the World Behind costar Mahershala Ali were asked about parenting.\n\n“I have an immense amount of appreciation for both of my older kids because they still allow me to be the same mom to them and it's not eye-rolling. There's a huge amount of understanding,” she said.\n\n“I parent them the same way out of the house that I parent them in the house. Which is, ‘Are you getting enough sleep? You sound like you're sick, are you drinking tea?’ And, ‘Text me when you get home so I can see that you're safe and sound.’”\n\nNever miss a story — sign up for PEOPLE's free daily newsletter to stay up-to-date on the best of what PEOPLE has to offer, from juicy celebrity news to compelling human interest stories.\n\nModer also came up in conversation with the hosts of The View on Monday. Roberts revealed there are “a few secrets” to maintaining her happy marriage, citing her sister Lisa Roberts Gillan.\n\n“My sister, who has been married for 25 years or 26 years, I think, she says the secret to a happy marriage is two bathroom sinks and two phone lines,” the actress said.\n\n“I think marrying the right person is important,” she added. “Lots of kissing hello and goodbye is really, I think, a critical detail to daily life... Everybody try it. Give it a week. Every time you say good morning, a hug and a kiss.”\n\nThe View co-host Whoopi Goldberg chimed in: “Maybe that’s been my problem! I just do a kiss out the side of her mouth. ‘See ya, bye. Come back in a week.’”\n\nGoldberg, who has joked about her three marriages and preference for single life, added, “Hit and run, that’s what I like!”\n\nRoberts also praised Goldberg on an upcoming film of hers that Moder worked on. “My husband, who’s a cinematographer, he filmed this beautiful movie called Ezra,” she said, pointing to Goldberg. “And you are so doggone great in that movie.”\n\nAlthough she’s largely kept her family life out of the spotlight, Roberts has attended starry events with Moder and shared family birthday tributes on social media. The Ticket to Paradise star told PEOPLE in 2021 about what brings her joy: \"Pure happiness is the feeling one has when the people they love are happy.”"
